.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-INCLUDE 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-include \- stage changes or save them to a batch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch include
[\fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-file\fR [\fIPATH\fR] | \fB\-\-files\fR \fIPATTERN\fR...]
[\fB\-\-from\fR \fIBATCH\fR | \fB\-\-to\fR \fIBATCH\fR]
[\fB\-\-auto\-advance\fR|\fB\-\-no\-auto\-advance\fR]
.PP
.B git-stage-batch include
[\fB\-\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR | \fB\-\-line\fR \fIIDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-as\fR \fITEXT\fR | \fB\-\-as\-stdin\fR]
[\fB\-\-no\-edge\-overlap\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B include
stages selected live changes. With
.B \-\-to
it saves live changes to a batch instead of staging them. With
.B \-\-from
it applies batch changes to the index and working tree.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-\-line, \-\-lines " IDS
Stage or save only specific displayed line IDs.
.TP
.B \-\-file
.RI [ PATH ]
Operate on one complete file. If
.I PATH
is omitted, use the selected hunk's file.
.TP
.BI "\-\-files " PATTERN "..."
Operate on all changed files matched by gitignore-style patterns.
.TP
.BI "\-\-from " BATCH
Stage changes from
.IR BATCH .
To include a reviewed ambiguity resolution, use
.IR BATCH :include: N
with
.BR \-\-file .
The
.IR BATCH :apply: N
selector belongs to
.B apply
and is rejected here.
.TP
.BI "\-\-to " BATCH
Save selected live changes to
.IR BATCH .
The batch is created if needed.
.TP
.BI "\-\-as " TEXT
Stage replacement text for selected lines, or stage
.I TEXT
as the full file content when used with
.BR \-\-file .
.TP
.B \-\-as\-stdin
Read replacement text from standard input exactly, preserving trailing
newlines.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-edge\-overlap
Do not strip unchanged edge-overlap lines from replacement text used with
.BR "\-\-line \-\-as" .
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-advance
Select the next hunk after the command completes.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-advance
Leave no hunk selected after the command completes.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
git-stage-batch include
git-stage-batch include --line 1,3,5-7
git-stage-batch include --file src/app.py
git-stage-batch include --to cleanup --files 'src/**'
git-stage-batch include --from cleanup --file src/app.py
git-stage-batch show --from cleanup:include:2 --file src/app.py
git-stage-batch include --from cleanup:include:2 --file src/app.py
some-command | git-stage-batch include --line 1-3 --as-stdin
.fi
.RE
.SH CANDIDATES
If a plain
.B include --from
operation finds multiple safe structural placements, it refuses without
changing either the index or working tree and points to
.B show --from
.IR BATCH :include .
Review the candidate overview, or preview a numbered candidate, then include
that same reviewed candidate.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-show (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-discard (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-apply (1)
